The '''prefatory note''', labeled '''Author's Note''' in some editions, refers to the untitled preface placed before the first chapter of ''[[The Hobbit]]''.

The prefatory note starts with ''THE HOBBIT OR THERE AND BACK AGAIN'' written in [[Cirth]]. It proceeds to discuss some issues related to the words ''[[dwarf]]'' and ''[[orc]]''. Then it gives a short description of the Cirth writing system used in ''The Hobbit''. The letters of the [[moon-runes]], read by [[Elrond]] in [[Rivendell]], are provided in the end.

==History==
The note was first added to the [http://tolkienbooks.net/php/details.php?reference=21200 second edition of ''The Hobbit''] ([[1951]]).<ref>{{HM|RC}}, p. lxviii</ref> In [[1966]], a completely revised prefatory note first appeared in the [http://tolkienbooks.net/php/details.php?reference=21450 Longmans/Unwin] edition.<ref>{{HM|AH}}, p. 28</ref> The latter text has been used since.

